            <heading>Amendment of the Non-Domestic Rating (Valuation of Utilities) (Scotland) Order 2005</heading>
            <article eId="article-2">
               <num>2.</num>
               <content>
                  <p>The Non-Domestic Rating (Valuation of Utilities) (Scotland) Order 2005<noteRef href="#f00003" class="footnote" marker="3"/> is amended in accordance with articles 3 to 6.</p>
               </content>
            </article>
            <article eId="article-3">
               <num>3.</num>
               <content>
                  <p>For article 2(1)(b)(ii) (electricity generation) substitute—<mod>
                        <quotedStructure startQuote="“" endQuote="”" ukl:TargetClass="unknown" ukl:TargetSubClass="unknown" ukl:Context="unknown">
                           <subparagraph>
                              <num>(ii)</num>
                              <content>
                                 <p>the primary source of energy in such generation is biomass, the use of wind, wave, water, tidal or solar power, or the burning of refuse.</p>
                              </content>
                           </subparagraph>
                        </quotedStructure>
                     </mod>
                     <inline name="AppendText">.</inline>
                  </p>
               </content>
            </article>
